    "is confined to pre-trained models whereas our survey covers all deep neural networks employed for software engineering tasks.Zhang et al. [26] conducted a systematic survey to summarize the current state-of-the-art research in the large language model (LLM)-based software engineering (SE) community.",
    "They summarized 30 representative LLMs of source code across three model architectures, 15 pre-training objectives across four categories, and 16 downstream tasks across five categories.",
    "They presented a detailed summarization of the recent SE studies for which LLMs are commonly utilized.",
    "Furthermore, they summarized existing attempts to empirically evaluate LLMs in SE, such as benchmarks and empirical studies.",
    "Finally, they discussed several critical aspects of optimization and applications of LLMs in SE."
